India ' s reserves cross $ 19 bln - Chidambaram . Indian Finance Minister P . Chidambaram said on Tuesday the country ' s foreign reserves crossed $ 19 billion last week . He was speaking at a economic editors ' conference . On Saturday , the Reserve Bank of India said foreign currency assets as on October 31 , 1996 totalled $ 19 . 16 billion against $ 17 . 04 billion as on March 31 , 1996 . 
